{
  "stem": "7458.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 121,
      "text": "In the middle of the darkest night, I could find my way in the forest to our bunker.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 122,
      "text": "I don't know how, but somehow we developed a sixth sense.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 123,
      "text": "And I ran, and I ran maybe five, six miles without stopping.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 124,
      "text": "And when I got near the bunker I started hollering to Chonen and the other guy, Ruvak is dead, because I assumed that he got shot, because when I-- when the firing stopped, and everything was quiet, I called out, Ruvak, Ruvak, and he didn't answer, so I assumed that he was dead.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 125,
      "text": "And I hollered out, Ruvak is dead.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 126,
      "text": "And I told the other two what had happened.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 127,
      "text": "And we decided to wait about an hour and then to go look for his body.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 128,
      "text": "And about half an hour later, Ruvak came running.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 129,
      "text": "And before he reached the bunker, he hollered, Berl is dead.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 130,
      "text": "They used to call me Berl.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 131,
      "text": "He thought I was dead, so he was hollering that I was dead.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 132,
      "text": "And I thought he was dead.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 133,
      "text": "And so that-- that was how we had to gather food if we were to-- to survive day by day.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 134,
      "text": "It was nothing but filth and hunger, starvation and danger.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 135,
      "text": "There was hardly anybody who was willing to give us shelter.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 136,
      "text": "I should say that during this period, there were two families-- the one I've already mentioned who stopped me from going to Jasionowka to be shot-- and then another one, a Mrs.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 137,
      "text": "Dekar, who eventually gave us shelter in a barn with Ruvak and the others.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 138,
      "text": "And again, we dug a hole in the barn, similar construction, and we were hiding in her barn and going out and begging for food.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 139,
      "text": "But they took their own lives in their hands [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] giving us shelter.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
